<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="237" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Description</emphasis>
. A very small incomplete specimen (12 chaetigers) (
<figureCitation box="[932,1055,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,851,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-285@6.[188,1399,849,1865]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Syllis maganda n. sp. Paratypes (MNCN 16.01/18687). Scanning Electron Micrographs (A, B, D), digital camera (C). A), C) specimen of Haplosyllis sp. (arrows) which is feeding on a posterior dorsal cirrus of Syllis maganda n. sp. B) detail of simple chaeta of Haplosyllis sp. D) regeneration of the prostomium (arrow) of Syllis maganda n. sp., ventral view. No scale bar in digital camera photo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4403044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4403044/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Fig. 2A, C</figureCitation>
, arrows), with 1-2 simple chaetae per parapodium; chaetae with short spur and two very long, strongly curved teeth, very close to each other, the subdistal with round tip, the distal with pointed tip (
<figureCitation box="[693,781,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[188,1397,851,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-285@6.[188,1399,849,1865]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Syllis maganda n. sp. Paratypes (MNCN 16.01/18687). Scanning Electron Micrographs (A, B, D), digital camera (C). A), C) specimen of Haplosyllis sp. (arrows) which is feeding on a posterior dorsal cirrus of Syllis maganda n. sp. B) detail of simple chaeta of Haplosyllis sp. D) regeneration of the prostomium (arrow) of Syllis maganda n. sp., ventral view. No scale bar in digital camera photo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4403044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4403044/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Remarks</emphasis>
. The highly characteristic shape of the chaetae does not fit with any other described species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langerhans" authorityYear="1879" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Haplosyllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We only have a single, incomplete, minute specimen, and precludes a formal description. There are some other small, similar species in the Pacific, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Aguado, San Martin &amp; Nishi, 2006" authorityName="Aguado, San Martin &amp; Nishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[672,1369,511,537]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="crassicirrata">
<emphasis box="[672,954,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Haplosyllis crassicirrata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Aguado, M. T. &amp; San Martin, G. &amp; Nishi, E." box="[961,1369,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="9 - 16" refId="ref15442" refString="Aguado, M. T., San Martin, G. &amp; Nishi, E. (2006) Two new species of Syllidae (Polychaeta) from Japan. Scientia Marina, 70, 9 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2006.70 s 39" type="journal article" year="2006">Aguado, San Martín &amp; Nishi, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,548,574]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Japan</collectingCountry>
; however, that species has thick dorsal cirri, the distal teeth are more acute and more separated (
<bibRefCitation author="Aguado, M. T. &amp; San Martin, G. &amp; Nishi, E." pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="9 - 16" refId="ref15442" refString="Aguado, M. T., San Martin, G. &amp; Nishi, E. (2006) Two new species of Syllidae (Polychaeta) from Japan. Scientia Marina, 70, 9 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2006.70 s 39" type="journal article" year="2006">
Aguado 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Sarda, Avila &amp; Paul, 2002" authorityName="Sarda, Avila &amp; Paul" authorityYear="2002" box="[231,775,583,612]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="basticola">
<emphasis box="[231,469,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Haplosyllis basticola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sarda, R. &amp; Avila, C. &amp; Paul, V. J." box="[476,775,583,612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="165 - 175" refId="ref22938" refString="Sarda, R., Avila, C. &amp; Paul, V. J. (2002) An association between a syllid polychaete, Haplosyllis basticola n. sp., and the sponge Ianthella basta. Micronesica, 34 (2), 165 - 175." type="journal article" year="2002">Sardá, Ávila &amp; Paul, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[848,916,583,609]" name="Guam" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Guam</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[932,1062,583,610]" name="Micronesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
) has the chaetae with shorter and not so curved teeth (
<bibRefCitation author="Sarda, R. &amp; Avila, C. &amp; Paul, V. J." box="[378,574,619,646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="165 - 175" refId="ref22938" refString="Sarda, R., Avila, C. &amp; Paul, V. J. (2002) An association between a syllid polychaete, Haplosyllis basticola n. sp., and the sponge Ianthella basta. Micronesica, 34 (2), 165 - 175." type="journal article" year="2002">
Sardá 
<emphasis box="[450,499,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Cepeda &amp; Lattig, 2017" authorityName="Cepeda &amp; Lattig" authorityYear="2017" box="[592,1059,619,645]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="leylae">
<emphasis box="[592,793,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Haplosyllis leylae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cepeda, D. &amp; Martin, D. &amp; Britayev, T. A. &amp; Al-Aidaroos, A. M. &amp; Lattig, P." box="[800,1059,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="1123 - 1129" refId="ref17067" refString="Cepeda, D., Martin, D., Britayev, T. A., Al-Aidaroos, A. M. &amp; Lattig, P. (2017) Haplosyllis (Annelida: Syllidae) from Saudi Arabian Red Sea, with the description of a new endosymbiotic species and a dichotomous key for the Indo-Pacific species. Marine Biodiversity, 47, 1123 - 1129. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 017 - 0675 - 6" type="journal article" year="2017">Cepeda &amp; Lattig, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Red Sea, is also a small species with short dorsal cirri, but the chaetae have longer and larger spurs and the teeth are not as long and curved as in the specimen from the 
<collectingCountry box="[467,593,691,717]" name="Philippines" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cepeda, D. &amp; Martin, D. &amp; Britayev, T. A. &amp; Al-Aidaroos, A. M. &amp; Lattig, P." box="[607,824,691,718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" pagination="1123 - 1129" refId="ref17067" refString="Cepeda, D., Martin, D., Britayev, T. A., Al-Aidaroos, A. M. &amp; Lattig, P. (2017) Haplosyllis (Annelida: Syllidae) from Saudi Arabian Red Sea, with the description of a new endosymbiotic species and a dichotomous key for the Indo-Pacific species. Marine Biodiversity, 47, 1123 - 1129. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 017 - 0675 - 6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Cepeda 
<emphasis box="[700,749,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Habitat</emphasis>
. The specimen has the everted pharynx attached to a posterior dorsal cirrus of a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martínez &amp; Martín, 2020" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Martín" authorityYear="2020" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="maganda" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Syllis maganda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[262,322,764,790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
